{
  // ROOT TypeScript configuration
  //
  // ⚠️ ARCHITECTURE DECISION: Multiple TypeScript Configs ⚠️
  //
  // This Electron app uses SEPARATE TypeScript configs for different processes:
  // - tsconfig.base.json     → Shared settings (DRY principle)
  // - tsconfig.main.json     → Main process (Node.js environment)
  // - tsconfig.renderer.json → Renderer process (Browser environment)
  //
  // WHY NOT A SINGLE CONFIG?
  // 1. Type Safety: Main process shouldn't access DOM, renderer shouldn't access fs
  // 2. Security: Prevents accidental Node.js usage in renderer (security risk)
  // 3. Build Tools: webpack.main.config.js specifically uses tsconfig.main.json
  //
  // EXAMPLE ERRORS THIS PREVENTS:
  // - In main process: window.alert() → TypeScript error (no DOM)
  // - In renderer: require('fs') → TypeScript error (no Node.js)
  //
  // DO NOT MERGE THESE CONFIGS - it would break type safety!

  // This file now uses TypeScript Project References for the solution
  // TypeScript configurations are now organized within each subproject directory:
  // - src/main/tsconfig.json     → Main process configuration
  // - src/renderer/tsconfig.json → Renderer process configuration
  // - config/tsconfig.base.json  → Shared base configuration (DRY principle)
  "files": [],
  "references": [
    { "path": "./src/main/tsconfig.json" },
    { "path": "./src/renderer/tsconfig.json" }
  ]
}